<TITLE> Four Nordic countries pledge Tk 38 crore in Sidr aid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 24 (bdnews24.com)  Pledges of relief funds for the victims of Cyclone Sidr continue to come in with four Nordic countries and the British-Bangladesh Chamber of Commerce adding their names to the growing list Friday. Norway, Sweden, Denmark and Iceland will together provide about Tk 38 crore while the BBCC and Oxfam will give about Tk 29 crore. "The managing director of BBCC Azizur Rahman has assured us that his organisation and Oxfam will primarily contribute 2 million," Bangladesh high commissioner in London Ashraf Uddin told bdnews24.com by e-mail. The high commissioner added that the amount might be increased in the future. Sweden will contribute Tk 7.76 crore and Denmark will add Tk 6.93 crore to the relief funds while Iceland will make Tk 33.5 lakh available. Norway will contribute Tk 23.17 crore to the relief efforts, said a statement received from the Bangladesh Embassy in Sweden. bdn
